During vblank, the PPU is "off", so it never puts anything on the PPU address bus (except for the "vram address").  The counter shouldn't clock by itself then.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Sat Mar 14, 2009 1:07 pm</p><hr />
